---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout
  title="Desktop app — decod.ing"
  description="Download the offline decod.ing desktop workbench for macOS, Windows, and Linux."
>
  <section class="page-hero container narrow">
    <span class="eyebrow">Offline desktop workbench</span><h1>
      One shortcut away from all 47 tools.
    </h1><p>
      The desktop shell adds an explicit global shortcut, one-time clipboard detection, local files,
      multiple windows, and signed manual updates.
    </p>
  </section>
  <section class="container download-grid">
    <article>
      <span class="platform">macOS</span><h2>Universal app</h2><p>
        Apple Silicon and Intel. Notarized distribution is published after signing credentials and
        beta gates are available.
      </p><button class="button secondary" disabled>Signed build pending</button>
    </article><article>
      <span class="platform">Windows</span><h2>x64 / arm64</h2><p>
        MSI/NSIS follows macOS stabilization and Windows code-signing verification.
      </p><button class="button secondary" disabled>Quality gate pending</button>
    </article><article>
      <span class="platform">Linux</span><h2>AppImage / deb</h2><p>
        Linux follows the macOS and Windows privacy and crash gates.
      </p><button class="button secondary" disabled>Quality gate pending</button>
    </article>
  </section>
</Layout>
